  "prompt": "Can you check your WhatsApp from another phone?",
  "response": "Yes, you can check your WhatsApp from another phone by using the following methods:\n\n1. **WhatsApp Web or Desktop:**\n   - On the second phone, open a web browser and go to web.whatsapp.com.\n   - On your primary phone, open WhatsApp and go to Settings > Linked Devices > Link a Device.\n   - Scan the QR code displayed on the second phone's browser with your primary phone.\n\n2. **Using WhatsApp's Multi-Device Feature:**\n   - Ensure your WhatsApp app is updated to the latest version on both phones.\n   - On your primary phone, go to WhatsApp > Settings > Linked Devices > Link a Device.\n   - On the second phone, install WhatsApp and instead of registering your number, choose the \"Link to Existing Account\" option.\n   - Scan the QR code on the second phone with your primary phone.\n\nRemember, your primary phone needs to be connected to the internet periodically for the multi-device feature to work seamlessly.",
